const pageTitle = 'House Removals Bristol – Quote in 47 Secs';
const pageDescription = `Bristol's trusted removal company since 1978. Professional home removals, packing, storage and more. ${siteConfig.company.rating.value}★ rated. Get your free quote in under a minute.`;

// ── Services Data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

const services = [
  {
    imageName: 'home-removals/Bristol-home-removals-service-1',
    title: 'Home Removals',
    description: `Moving home is one of the most significant events in anyone's life, and at Painless Removals we treat every house move with the attention and respect it deserves. Whether you're relocating from a compact two-bedroom flat in Clifton to a spacious family home in Long Ashton, or moving from a terraced house in Bedminster to a countryside property in the Chew Valley, our experienced team handles every step of the process so you don't have to worry about a thing.

Every home removal begins with a thorough pre-move survey — either in person or via video call — so we understand the exact scope of your move. We assess the number of rooms, the volume of furniture, any access challenges such as narrow staircases, tight parking, or listed building restrictions, and we plan the logistics accordingly. This means the quote you receive is accurate, transparent, and tailored specifically to your move — no nasty surprises on the day.

On moving day, your dedicated crew arrives with the right number of vans, professional-grade blankets, straps, and protective covers for every piece of furniture. We carefully disassemble beds, wardrobes, and shelving units, wrap each item individually, and load everything methodically to prevent shifting during transit. Mattresses go into sealed protectors, sofas into fitted covers, and televisions into padded bags — all included at no extra cost.

At your new home, we reverse the process with equal care. Furniture is reassembled in the rooms you choose, boxes are placed exactly where you want them, and we make sure everything is set up before we leave. For chain moves, we allocate a full day — so if solicitors run late or keys are delayed, there's no pressure and no rush. Your crew stays until the job is done properly, however long that takes.

We also coordinate with our packing team, cleaners, and storage facility so that every element of your move runs seamlessly together. One point of contact, one trusted team, one completely painless experience from start to finish.`,
    link: '/home-removals-bristol',
    linkText: 'How our home removals work →',
  },
  {
    imageName: 'packing/Bristol-home-packing-service',
    title: 'Packing Services',
    description: `Packing is the part of moving that most people dread — and for good reason. It takes far longer than you expect, it's physically exhausting, and if it's not done properly, your belongings are at risk of damage during transit. That's exactly why our professional packing service exists: to take the most stressful, time-consuming part of your move completely off your hands.

Our trained packing team arrives the day before your move, equipped with high-quality materials designed to protect every type of item. We use double-walled cardboard boxes, acid-free tissue paper for delicate items, bubble wrap for fragile glassware and ceramics, wardrobe boxes that let your clothes travel on hangers, and specialist picture boxes for artwork and mirrors. Every item is individually wrapped, clearly labelled by room, and packed in a logical order that makes unpacking at the other end quick and straightforward.

We handle everything from the kitchen — where most of the fragile items live — to the garage, loft, and garden shed. Books, vinyl collections, ornaments, electronics, lampshades, pot plants — nothing is too awkward or too delicate for our team. We've packed grand pianos, antique clocks, vintage wine collections, and family heirlooms passed down through generations. Whatever matters to you matters to us.

One of the biggest advantages of professional packing is insurance. When our team packs your belongings, every item is fully covered under our comprehensive goods-in-transit policy. If you pack items yourself, they're not covered to the same extent. So our packing service doesn't just save you time and effort — it gives you genuine peace of mind.

We offer full packing, part packing, and fragile-only packing options depending on your budget and how much you want to handle yourself. Many customers choose to pack their own clothes and personal items while we take care of the kitchen, living room, and anything breakable. There's no rigid package — we tailor the service to suit exactly what you need.`,
    link: '/home-packing-service',
    linkText: 'Our packing options →',
  },
  {
    imageName: 'storage/painless-removals-storage',
    title: 'Storage',
    description: `Sometimes the timing of a move doesn't quite line up. Perhaps your completion date has been pushed back, your new build isn't ready yet, or you're downsizing and need time to decide what to keep. Whatever the reason, our secure Bristol storage facility gives you the breathing room you need without adding stress to an already busy period.

Our warehouse is purpose-built for storing household goods. It's dry, clean, alarmed, and monitored around the clock with CCTV. Your belongings are loaded into individual sealed containers — not stacked loose in a shared warehouse — so nothing gets mixed up, nothing gets dusty, and nothing gets damaged. Each container is clearly labelled and logged so we can locate your items quickly when you need them back.

What sets our storage apart from self-storage is convenience. Because we're a removals company first and foremost, we can collect your items as part of your move and deliver them directly into storage without you having to make a separate trip. When you're ready, we bring everything back to your new home, unload, and set up — all in one seamless process. There's no hiring a van, no driving back and forth, and no heavy lifting on your part.

We offer flexible terms to suit your situation. Whether you need storage for a week, a month, or a year, you're never locked into a long contract. Your first month's storage is included free when you book a removal with us, and after that you pay a simple monthly rate with no hidden fees.

Access is available by appointment, so if you need to retrieve something specific or add more items, just give us a call and we'll arrange a time that works for you. Many customers use our storage during renovations, between property sales, or while travelling abroad — and appreciate knowing their possessions are in safe hands until they're ready for them.`,
    link: '/storage-service',
    linkText: 'Storage solutions →',
  },
  {
    imageName: 'house-clearance/Bristol-clearance-service-2',
    title: 'House Clearance',
    description: `Clearing a property can be an overwhelming task, especially when it comes during a difficult time. Whether you're dealing with a probate property after losing a loved one, preparing a home for sale, helping an elderly relative downsize, or simply clearing years of accumulated belongings from a property, our house clearance service handles the entire process with sensitivity, efficiency, and respect.

We begin every clearance with an on-site assessment so we understand the scope of the job and can provide an accurate, fixed-price quote. There are no hourly rates that spiral out of control and no surprise charges on the day. Once you've agreed to the price, our team arrives on the scheduled date and works methodically through every room, loft, garage, shed, and outbuilding.

We don't just throw everything into a skip. Our approach prioritises responsible disposal: items in good condition are donated to local charities and community organisations, recyclable materials are sorted and sent to the appropriate facilities, and only genuinely unsalvageable waste goes to landfill. If there are items you'd like to keep, we can set those aside, pack them, and either deliver them to you or place them in our secure storage facility.

For probate clearances, we understand the emotional weight of the task. Our team works respectfully and carefully, and we'll always check with you before disposing of anything that might have sentimental or financial value. We've handled hundreds of probate clearances across Bristol and the surrounding area, and we know that a compassionate, unhurried approach makes all the difference during what is often a very difficult period.

We also offer partial clearances — perhaps you only need the loft and garage cleared, or a few rooms emptied before renovation work begins. The service is completely flexible and can be combined with our removals, cleaning, and storage services for a fully coordinated solution. From a single room to an entire estate, we make property clearance straightforward and stress-free.`,
    link: '/house-and-waste-clearance',
    linkText: 'House clearance services →',
  },
  {
    imageName: 'office-removals/Office-removals-Bristol-main',
    title: 'Office Removals',
    description: `Relocating an office is a very different challenge to moving a home. There are IT systems to disconnect and reconnect, sensitive documents to transport securely, specialist furniture to disassemble, and — most importantly — a business to keep running throughout the process. At Painless Removals, we've been handling commercial relocations across Bristol and the South West for decades, and we understand that minimising downtime is the absolute priority.

Every office move starts with a detailed planning meeting. We visit your current premises, assess the volume of furniture, equipment, and files, identify any access restrictions at both sites, and create a phased move plan that works around your business hours. For many clients, this means working evenings, weekends, or carrying out the move in stages so that some departments can continue operating while others are relocated.

Our team is experienced with the specialist equipment found in modern offices. Server racks, multi-screen workstations, printers, copiers, telephone systems, and networking hardware are all handled with appropriate care. We use anti-static packaging for sensitive electronics, padded crates for monitors and screens, and clearly labelled cable management systems so that your IT team can reconnect everything quickly at the new location.

Desks, boardroom tables, reception counters, and modular furniture systems are carefully disassembled, wrapped, transported, and reassembled in your new layout. We work from floor plans and desk allocation sheets so that every item ends up exactly where it should be, and your staff can sit down and start working as soon as they arrive.

We also handle the logistics that many businesses overlook: archive box delivery in advance so your team can pack personal items and files, recycling and disposal of old furniture you're not taking with you, and coordination with building management at both sites to arrange loading bay access, lift reservations, and floor protection. The result is a smooth, professional relocation that lets you focus on your business while we handle the heavy lifting.`,
    link: '/office-removals',
    linkText: 'Office & commercial moves →',
  },
  {
    imageName: 'cleaning/cleaning-service',
    title: 'Cleaning',
    description: `The last thing anyone wants to think about after a long moving day is going back to clean the property they've just left. But whether you're a tenant trying to secure your deposit back, a homeowner wanting to leave the place spotless for the new buyers, or a landlord preparing a property for the next occupant, a thorough end-of-tenancy clean is often essential — and it's a job best left to professionals.

Our cleaning team works to professional end-of-tenancy standards that satisfy letting agents, landlords, and inventory clerks. Every room is deep-cleaned from top to bottom: kitchens are degreased, ovens and hobs are scrubbed inside and out, bathrooms are descaled and sanitised, windows are cleaned inside, carpets are vacuumed and spot-treated, and all surfaces, skirting boards, light switches, and door frames are wiped down. We don't cut corners, and we don't leave until the property meets the standard required.

What makes our cleaning service different is how seamlessly it integrates with your move. Because we're a removals company, we can schedule the clean to happen immediately after our crew finishes loading. While you travel to your new home with your belongings, our cleaning team moves in behind you and transforms the empty property. By the time you're unpacking at the other end, your old place is already spotless and ready for handover. There's no need to make a separate trip back, no juggling schedules with an independent cleaning company, and no risk of delays holding up your key return.

We also offer new-home cleans for customers who want their new property freshened up before they move in. This is particularly popular with buyers of older properties or rentals where the previous occupant's cleaning standards may not match your own. Our team can clean the new property the day before your move so that everything is fresh, hygienic, and welcoming when your furniture arrives.

The service is available as a standalone booking or as part of a complete moving package — and when bundled with your removal, you benefit from coordinated scheduling and a single point of contact for the entire process.`,
    link: '/cleaning-service',
    linkText: 'Moving day cleaning →',
  },
